		<guid isPermaLink="false">/?p=65404</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[You can now show and hide the mouse cursor on Windows and OS X desktop builds. Learn how!]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Starting with <a href=https://developer.coronalabs.com/downloads/daily-builds/ target="_blank">Daily Build 2016.2813</a>, you can now show and hide the mouse cursor in both OS X and Windows desktop builds. To hide the cursor, call:</p><pre class="crayon-plain-tag">native.setProperty( &quot;mouseCursorVisible&quot;, false )</pre><p>To show it again, call the function again with <code>true</code> as the second parameter.</p><pre class="crayon-plain-tag">native.setProperty( &quot;mouseCursorVisible&quot;, true )</pre><p>This completes the <a href=http://feedback.coronalabs.com/forums/188732-corona-sdk-feature-requests-feedback/suggestions/11294433-optionally-hide-os-cursor-in-desktop-builds target="_blank">Optionally Hide OS Cursor in Desktop Builds</a> feedback request. If you have questions or need help, please discuss further it in the <a href=https://forums.coronalabs.com/topic/61330-from-the-blog-hiding-the-cursor-in-os-x-and-windows-desktop-builds/ target="_blank">forums</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
]]></content:encoded>
